-- Mexico Stocks: Empresas Ica, Grupo Mexico, Penoles Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-01T01:01:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/mexico-stocks-empresas-ica-grupo-mexico-penoles-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC  index  fell 0.5 percent to 37,816.69.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s biggest
construction company, fell 4 percent to 23.59 pesos. Shares have
declined every day since the company’s Feb. 27 earnings report,
which showed total debt increased in the fourth quarter.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, fell 2 percent to 40.49 pesos. Copper for May
delivery declined in New York.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, slipped 3.1 percent to 637.41 pesos. Silver
futures for May delivery fell in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
